A suspected internet fraudster has been shot dead by yet-to-be identified assailants along Orhuwhorun Road in Udu Local Government Area of Delta State. It was gathered that the deceased was cruising in his car, a white Toyota Venza, when the gunmen suspected to be assassins, struck on Saturday. A source said “nothing was taken away from him after killing him. They seemed to have followed him from somewhere; nobody knows.   2023: Organisation urges youths to vote out bad leaders     ‘Council poll: Police announce restriction of movement’     Group praises NEDC over water points for cattle   “The young man is a Yahoo boy who picked money for someone, but refused to give the money to the person (whom he picked it for). “The man did not die instantly. After being shot he drove on and hit a BEDC pole before he died right inside his car along Orhuwhorun Road, before Tipper Garage.” Police spokesman DSP Bright Edafe confirmed the incident yesterday in a text message.